Got it — your date filter won’t work until you have an actual date column to filter on.

Right now your reports table in v2 has:
	•	created_at (string)
	•	updated_at (string)

✅ We will filter using updated_at (best for “latest changes reflected”).

1) Add these 2 inputs in dashboard.html (inside your filter form)

<div>
  <label class="muted">From date</label>
  <input type="date" name="from_date" value="{{ request.args.get('from_date','') }}">
</div>

<div>
  <label class="muted">To date</label>
  <input type="date" name="to_date" value="{{ request.args.get('to_date','') }}">
</div>

2) Add this EXACT block in app.py inside dashboard() (after reading args)

Add these lines near the top:

from_date = request.args.get("from_date", "").strip()
to_date = request.args.get("to_date", "").strip()

3) Add these filters in SQL building (IMPORTANT)

Put this in your dashboard() after other filters:

if from_date:
    sql += " AND date(r.updated_at) >= date(?)"
    params.append(from_date)

if to_date:
    sql += " AND date(r.updated_at) <= date(?)"
    params.append(to_date)

4) WHY it was not working
	•	HTML didn’t send from/to dates (no inputs)
	•	Backend didn’t read them (request.args)
	•	SQL didn’t filter using date() conversion

5) Quick test (do exactly)
	1.	Open dashboard
	2.	Choose From = today
	3.	Choose To = today
	4.	Click Apply
✅ You should see only reports updated today.

⸻

If you want “Month filter” also, tell me what format you want:
	•	dropdown like Jan 2026
	•	or automatic based on From/To only
